{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17621013","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17621013"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T15:48:57+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T15:48:57+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16664"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"16664","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/16664"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.65,0.05,0.15,0,0.15]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9355"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"75915"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"9355","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/9355"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16664"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"61422"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"38"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"5326"},{"type":"tags","id":"5460"},{"type":"tags","id":"5503"},{"type":"tags","id":"5631"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"22144"},{"type":"contributions","id":"22147"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"75915","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/75915"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EHealth policy advocacy is an important skill for medical professionals who wish to create positive change in healthcare systems.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the primary purpose of health policy advocacy?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["To influence policy decisions through evidence-based recommendations","To develop policy frameworks for clinical research","To monitor healthcare regulations and ensure practice compliance","To manage health service budgets and resource allocation","To deliver clinical care services and improve patient outcomes"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe primary purpose of health policy advocacy is \u003Cstrong\u003Eto influence policy decisions through evidence-based recommendations\u003C/strong\u003E. This involves identifying important health issues, gathering evidence, engaging with stakeholders, and communicating effectively with decision-makers to promote positive change in healthcare systems.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe other options represent different aspects of healthcare:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ETo develop policy frameworks for clinical research\u003C/strong\u003E is focused on creating guidelines for conducting research rather than advocating for system-level change.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ETo monitor healthcare regulations and ensure practice compliance\u003C/strong\u003E describes the role of regulatory bodies like the Australian Health Practitioner Regulation Agency (AHPRA).\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ETo manage health service budgets and resource allocation\u003C/strong\u003E relates to healthcare administration and financial management.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ETo deliver clinical care services and improve patient outcomes\u003C/strong\u003E describes the direct clinical role of healthcare practitioners.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EEffective health policy advocacy requires understanding of health systems, evidence synthesis, stakeholder engagement, and strategic communication skills. The goal is to influence decision-makers to implement policies that improve health outcomes for communities and populations.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Policy advocacy involves systematic efforts to influence public policy decisions through evidence and strategic communication.","The key components of effective health policy advocacy are research evidence, stakeholder engagement, and clear communication of solutions.","Health professionals can influence population health outcomes by advocating for evidence-based health policies."],"references":["Rechtschaffen TH, Kapoor DA. Health Policy and Advocacy. Urol Clin North Am. 2021;48(2):251-258. doi:10.1016/j.ucl.2021.01.007 Available from: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/33795059/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"61422"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16664"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"61422","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/61422"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-01T13:49:13+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-01T13:51:19+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9355"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"75915"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"38","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/38"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83c\udf0f","name":"Public Health","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"6"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior"